The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) is expected to brief the media after conducting oversight visits to the Kusile and Medupi power stations this week. • Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) is expected to brief the media after conducting oversight visits to the Kusile and Medupi power stations this week. Eskom's performance in the past few years has concerned Scopa. There's been more than R19-billion in irregular expenditure and a ballooning debt of R380-billion in the 2017/2018 financial year. READ: Strings attached to Eskom bailout On Wednesday, Eskom announced that its Medupi power station’ unit one has produced 190 megawatts of power for the first time. This makes it the last of the six units to be synchronised to the national grid.